## AI Model Fallback Chain

Groq enforces rate limits per model. HMIND implements an automatic fallback so the chat never fails due to rate limiting:

```
llama-3.1-8b-instant   ← primary (fastest)
      │ rate limited?
      ▼
gemma2-9b-it
      │ rate limited?
      ▼
llama3-8b-8192
      │ rate limited?
      ▼
llama-3.2-3b-preview
      │ rate limited?
      ▼
llama-3.2-1b-preview
      │ rate limited?
      ▼
gemma-7b-it            ← last resort
```

Each fallback attempt is logged with which model was used. The `model_used` field in the messages table records this for every response.

